<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.AccessTesterHelper</api_name><caller_access>1</caller_access><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>This script contains the functions used by access tester application.</description><name>AccessTesterHelper</name><script><![CDATA[var AccessTesterHelper = Class.create();
AccessTesterHelper.prototype = {

    initialize: function(objType) {
        this.library = new global.CommonLibraryFunctions();
        this.table = "u_access_test_results";
        this.arrayUtil = new global.ArrayUtil();
    },

    /**
     * This function is used to return the list of tables in the instance after excluding system table
     *
     * @returns {string} - list of tables
     */

    getUserTables: function() {
        var property = gs.getProperty('access.test.parameters');
        var mainProperties = JSON.parse(property);
        var excludedTables = (mainProperties.excluded_tables_prefix.toString()).split(',');

        var options = {
            "table": "sys_db_object",
            "query": mainProperties.table_basic_filter.toString(),
            "field": "name"
        };
        var tables = [];
        var excludeTable = false;
        var allTables = (JSON.parse(this.library.getRecordsField(options))).result;

        for (var index = 0; index < allTables.length; index++) {
            if (JSUtil.notNil(allTables[index])) {

                for (var excludeIndex = 0; excludeIndex < excludedTables.length; excludeIndex++) {
                    if (allTables[index].indexOf(excludedTables[excludeIndex]) == 0) {
                        excludeTable = true;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if (!excludeTable) {
                    tables.push(allTables[index]);
                }
                excludeTable = false;
            }
        }
        tables.sort();
        return tables;

    },

    generateAccessResults: function(user) {

        this.impersonate(user);

        var tables = this.getUserTables();
        var testRun = this.getTestNumber();
        var accessObj = {};
        var answer = {};
        for (var i = 0; i < tables.length; i++) {
            var currentTable = tables[i];

            try {
                var grSecure = new GlideRecordSecure(currentTable);
                accessObj = {
                    "u_create": grSecure.canCreate(),
                    "u_read": grSecure.canRead(),
                    "u_update": grSecure.canWrite(),
                    "u_delete": grSecure.canDelete(),
                    "u_number": testRun,
                    "u_user": user,
                    "u_table": currentTable,
                };
                this.addAccessResult(accessObj);
                accessObj = {};
            } catch (err) {
                gs.log('Error in AccessTesterHelper-generateAccessResults:' + tables[i] + "--" + err.toString());
            }
        }

        if (tables.length) {
            answer = {
                "status": "success",
                "result": tables.length
            };
        } else {
            answer = {
                "status": "failed",
                "result": 0
            };
        }
        this.unimpersonate();

        return JSON.stringify(answer);
    },

    //DESIGN NOTE: Check old vs new results. Could have gone with array or object for better performance but adding nested loop for simplicity.
    compareAccessResults: function(paramString) {

        var params = JSON.parse(paramString);
        var processedNewResults = [];
        var accessObj = {};
        var testRun = this.getResultNumber();
        try {

            var getOldResults = new GlideRecord(this.table);
            getOldResults.addEncodedQuery('u_user=' + params.user + '^u_number=' + params.old_result);
            getOldResults.query();
            while (getOldResults.next()) {

                var getNewResults = new GlideRecord(this.table);
                getNewResults.addEncodedQuery('u_user=' + params.user + '^u_number=' + params.new_result + '^u_table=' + getOldResults.getValue('u_table'));
                getNewResults.setLimit(1);
                getNewResults.query();
                if (getNewResults.next()) {

                    processedNewResults.push(getNewResults.getValue('sys_id'));
                    accessObj = {
                        "u_create": (getOldResults.u_create == getNewResults.u_create) ? false : true,
                        "u_read": (getOldResults.u_read == getNewResults.u_read) ? false : true,
                        "u_update": (getOldResults.u_update == getNewResults.u_update) ? false : true,
                        "u_delete": (getOldResults.u_delete == getNewResults.u_delete) ? false : true,
                        "u_number": testRun,
                        "u_user": getNewResults.getValue('u_user'),
                        "u_table": getNewResults.getValue('u_table'),
                    };
                    this.addAccessResult(accessObj);
                    accessObj = {};

                }
            }

            var allNewResults = this.getAccessResultTable({
                "user": params.user,
                "number": params.new_result,
                "field": "sys_id"
            });

            if (processedNewResults.length != allNewResults.length) {
                var missingNewResults = this.arrayUtil.diff(allNewResults, processedNewResults);
                if (missingNewResults.length) {
                    this.copyAccessResult({
                        "number": testRun,
                        "filter": 'sys_idIN' + missingNewResults.toString(),
                        "comments": "Present only in new results"
                    });
                }
            }

        } catch (err) {
            gs.log('Error in AccessTesterHelper-compareAccessResults:' + err.toString());
        }

    },

    getTestNumber: function() {
        return new global.NumberManager(this.table).getNextObjNumberPadded();
    },

    getResultNumber: function() {
        return "R" + this.getTestNumber();
    },

    copyAccessResult: function(params) {
        var getResults = new GlideRecord(this.table);
        getResults.addEncodedQuery(params.filter);
        getResults.query();
        while (getResults.next()) {
            getResults.u_number = params.number;
            getResults.u_comments = params.comments;
            getResults.insert();
        }
    },

    getAccessResultTable: function(params) {
        var options = {
            "table": this.table,
            "query": "u_user=" + params.user + "^u_number=" + params.number,
            "field": params.field
        };
        var answer = JSON.parse(this.library.getRecordsField(options));
        return answer.result;
    },

    addAccessResult: function(params) {
        var accessRecord = new GlideRecord(this.table);
        accessRecord.initialize();

        for (var key in params) {
            accessRecord[key] = params[key];
        }

        accessRecord.insert();
    },

    unimpersonate: function() {
        gs.getSession().onlineUnimpersonate();
    },

    impersonate: function(user) {
        gs.getSession().impersonate(user);
    },

    scheduleAccessResults: function(user) {
        var scheduleDeletion = new global.ScheduleOnce();
        scheduleDeletion.script = "new global.AccessTesterHelper().generateAccessResults('" + user + "');";
        scheduleDeletion.setLabel("Find Access Job: " + user);
        scheduleDeletion.schedule();
    },

    scheduleAccessCompare: function(params) {
        var scheduleDeletion = new global.ScheduleOnce();
        scheduleDeletion.script = "new global.AccessTesterHelper().compareAccessResults('" + JSON.stringify(params) + "');";
        scheduleDeletion.setLabel("Compare Access Job: " + params.user);
        scheduleDeletion.schedule();
    },

    type: 'AccessTesterHelper'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-12-05 08:19:21</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_id>7cb0569ddb21001025cf56086896195c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>63</sys_mod_count><sys_name>AccessTesterHelper</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Access Testing" source="85298655db21001025cf560868961960">85298655db21001025cf560868961960</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Access Testing">85298655db21001025cf560868961960</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_7cb0569ddb21001025cf56086896195c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-06 17:32:13</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>
